sentences: Bruce & Terry was an American rock music duo from the 1960s.
In 1963, they began recording together and helped produce the album Surfin' Round the World.

While producing a "surf-frat" band called the Rip Chords, whose "Here I Stand" had reached No. 51 in early 1963, they ended up vocal arranging and singing all of the vocal parts on the band's hit "Hey Little Cobra" in 1964.
